SIMPLE: exactness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exactness
<hw>Ex*act"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition of
being exact; accuracy; nicety; precision; regularity; <as>as,
<ex>exactness</ex> of judgement or deportment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Careful observance of method and conformity to
truth; <as>as, <ex>exactness</ex> in accounts or
business</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had . . . that sort of <qex>exactness</qex> which would have
made him a respectable antiquary.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exactor</ent>⟦br⟧
